  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to examine removal of protein bound uremic substances by mFPSA in
      chronic hemodialysis patients. mFPSA is an extracorporal blood purification system developed
      for detoxification in acute liver failure by removal of protein bound as well as water
      soluble substances.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Measurements of uremic protein bound substances before and after mFPSA and a preceding
      routine hemodialysis session.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
